title: Part 3
content:
Part 3

1:00 P.M. THE event updated and revealed zero new supplies. This meant the phase for gathering supplies was completely over. The current locations of each class were Class A at D11, Class B at D12 and the Class C and D alliance at E10. As a result of the repeated attacks and retreats up to that point, the situation progressed to a point where all classes were rapidly closing in on each other. Though they hadn't made contact yet. Receiving a rapid-fire report from the analyst, Class A shouted to inform everyone of the restricted area. A little after 1:05 p.m., the VIP Yukimura received a new message from the commander and urged everyone to halt.

Barely fifty meters away from that exchange.

Class B, who advanced northward, also stopped in their tracks.

"Class A is right in front of us. They're probably a few dozen meters away. Everyone, stay sharp."

Katsuragi took a half step forward and quietly informed his classmates.

"Every single one of you better take down at least one of them before you get taken out. Now that we're this far, who gives a damn how many we beat in that first-day ambush? Any useless deadweight is a candidate for expulsion."

With those words, Ryuuen put intense pressure on them, firing them up and making them advance forward quietly.

One step, two steps. They moved forward, treading on dirt, leaves and small twigs.

"But are you sure about this, Katsuragi? We let one of Class A's VIPs get away..."

Ishizaki spoke up. A short while ago, Ryuuen immediately used tactics to identify the two GPS signals that had unnaturally separated from the main Class A group. Their identities were the escort, Miyake Akito and the VIP, Wang Mei-Yu.

"If three VIPs are taken out, it's a total wipeout. They probably split off to avoid the risk of being annihilated in a massive brawl. For us to send pursuers, we would similarly need a VIP and a guard—a minimum of two people. But in a two-on-two, there's no telling how it'll turn out. Miyake's athletic ability isn't bad, either. On top of that, it's not just Class A nearby; Class C and Class D are also approaching. Acting separately is far too dangerous."

While they wanted to defeat them if they could, Ryuuen judged it too risky to split off a small part of their forces to send after them in this situation. Class B staunchly maintained its stance of protecting the VIP with all its members.

"Something's off..."

At that, Katsuragi's expression tightened.

"Huh? What's off?"

They weren't engaging with the Class A group in front of them. It was taking longer than expected to make contact.

"We should be running into them any time now—this is a frustrating wait."

If they moved in any of the three directions other than south, where they would run into Class B, it wouldn't be difficult to avoid contact. If they fled, they wanted to pursue immediately, but they could only learn the other classes' latest movements every five minutes. They couldn't give chase right away without receiving the new locations.

Class B, which continued to advance slowly and with maximum caution, was informed of the latest positions by the commander five minutes later, but it was then that they learned a troublesome fact.

It was because Class A hadn't moved in any of the four cardinal directions.

"R-Ryuuen-kun... It says... Class A's GPS and our GPS are overlapping...!"

"So they used a tactic here, did they?"

For the next thirty minutes, they would be unable to track Class A. They knew that was a possibility, but it meant a period of extreme disadvantage for the other classes.

Katsuragi immediately gave orders to protect the VIPs from all four sides. This was because they couldn't afford to have their three VIPs taken out under any circumstances. Fortunately, in preparation for such a situation, Katsuragi made them learn several hand signals as a way to issue commands without speaking.

Having them retreat from the inevitable battle ahead was one option, but without their VIPs, they couldn't grasp the other classes' battle situations and if the guards were wiped out, they would eventually be cornered and defeated. In the end, it was most efficient to keep them close. At least, that was how Ryuuen was thinking and acting.

Would they run, or would they attack?

Everyone fell silent, holding their breath, so as to not miss the slightest footstep or any sign of trouble.

The VIP who received the information from the commander took a pre-prepared slip of paper and scribbled on it gently, careful not to tear a hole in it.

Then, they showed it to Ryuuen, who was standing nearby.

'C and D ahead'

It was news that even the allied classes, who'd been approaching in a pincer formation, were now close. If the vanished Class A circled around, the risk of Class B being caught in a pincer attack would increase.

Deciding there was no time to hesitate, Ryuuen made the decision to retreat south for the time being and just as he raised his arm to give the command—

"They're behind us!"

The one who shouted was Isoyama, who was in the rear. Multiple paintballs began to assault Class B from behind.

"They got behind us?! Fall back while returning fire! C and D are coming, hurry!"

Once things had gotten to that point, hand signals were meaningless, so Katsuragi shouted, simultaneously ordering them to fight and retreat. The battle with the enemy that got behind them began.

"No doubt about it! It's Class A! I saw Sudou!"

"H-haha—!"

Hearing her classmate's voice, Ibuki broke into a fierce, frightening smile.

"W-what's with that creepy laugh? You're givin' me the creeps, Ibuki!"

Ishizaki, hiding behind a tree with her, looked at Ibuki, slightly taken aback.

"You know, I honestly didn't give a damn about things like that ambush on Class C at the start."

She ejected the magazine from her submachine gun, confirmed that there were plenty of rounds left and then slammed it back deep into place with a clack.

"Because I've finally met the opponent I'm supposed to take down."

"Ooh... pretty ambitious for you. Thinkin' Class A is the biggest enemy, huh?"

"Huh? You think I care about crap like that? I've just been itching for a fight... because I wanted so, so badly to see that look of frustration on that Horikita girl's face!"

She said as she mercilessly fired paintballs from her submachine gun. A wristwatch alarm rang out, indicating she hit someone more than ten meters away.

When the magazine ran empty, she quickly removed it and reloaded a new one. Ibuki still had seven spare magazines she'd been saving up until then. She could shoot more than enough.

"All my pent-up grudges, I'm gonna pay them back right here, right now!"

"O-Oh. Well, I guess it's not a bad thing to be motivated... For now, I'm gonna back up a bit, so don't push yourse—What the...?"

It was inevitable that that place would soon become a danger zone and just as Ishizaki tried to fall back a little, Ibuki grabbed his arm and stopped him.

"You're my support."

"Huh? Give me a break. I've gotta protect Ryuuen-san."

"You don't need to protect a guy like that. More importantly, you're going to be my shield."

"No way in hell!"

"You're holding that big-ass weapon, so just charge in, will you?"

"If I go now, it's like I'm asking them to shoot me!"

"As long as I can take down Horikita, that's all that matters!"

"It's not all that matters!"

During their loud exchange, Class A also noticed the enemy students hiding behind the large tree and fired paintballs at them without mercy. A paintball faintly whizzed past the tip of Ishizaki's hair.

"Whoa, that was close!"

Ibuki glared at Ishizaki, who was breaking out in a cold sweat.

"If we wait here, we'll get taken out eventually, so go, Ishizaki! C'mon! Hurry up!"

"Agh, fine! I guess I've got no choice! Follow me, Ibuki!"

Ishizaki burst out and using his large build for cover, Ibuki stuck close behind him and burst out as well.

Meanwhile, on the other side, were the Class A students who'd used tactics to circle around to the rear. One of them, Sudou, had just taken out his fifth person.

"I'm out of ammo! Let me reload!"

Blessed with great physical ability and having polished his skills in practice to a level his classmates could not match, he was putting on an ace-level performance without holding back.

Yukimura, who was hiding nearby, handed Sudou a fully loaded magazine. As the designated VIP, Yukimura couldn't attack, but providing support didn't violate the rules.

"Class B is down to thirteen! The guy Sudou just took out was probably one of their VIPs!"

Information about eliminated students came in periodically over the radio.

"Oh, for real? That's lucky...! Just two more!"

"Ah, no, wait! It looks like we lost one, too. Mii-chan's out!"

His joy was short-lived; in the blink of an eye, the VIP count was two to two.

"What's the situation with Class C and Class D?"

"Hirata's holding them off now. It seems we anticipated their counter-strategy, just as Horikita read."

"That's Suzune for ya—"

Sudou smiled, overcome with delight, but then he heard multiple sets of footsteps approaching from the front.

"They're closing in! You stay hidden!"

He gave the order to Yukimura, then leaned his upper body out and aimed his gun at the approaching Class B students. Meanwhile, the Class B students, despite noticing Sudou, showed no sign of aiming at him and were all facing a different direction.

He landed a paintball on the abdomen of Nomura, who got the closest, but the remaining few forcefully broke past Sudou's flank.

"I won't let you get away!"

He aimed at their backs and took out one more, but the dense trees blocked the remaining two and he couldn't get a clear shot.

"Tch! I'm leaving this place to you guys!"

Leaving a few students with orders to protect Yukimura, Sudou gave chase to the two.

"There's Satou! Take her out, no matter what!"

Class C, Class D and Class B.

As if their objectives had aligned, all of their guns locked onto Satou.

But the next moment, as they pulled their triggers, Satou's figure vanished in an instant.

"Kya!"

It was by the hands of someone Satou herself had never expected.

"Are you okay?!"

Sudou pulled Satou into his arms, saving her from the predicament of being showered in paintballs.

"Y-Yeah, thank—!"

Before Satou could finish her thanks, even more paintballs grazed past them.

"They're comin' at us with everything they've got. Are they plannin' on using up all their ammo here?!"

Sudou fired back a few warning shots, but knowing he couldn't aim properly while protecting Satou, he quickly took his finger off the trigger.

"Don't you think somethin's weird...?"

"W-Weird?"

"Look at the paintball marks around us. It's obvious way more guns are pointed at us, right? Even though there are a bunch of other allies hidin' around."

He said, looking at Inogashira and Okitani hiding behind the large trees to their left and right a short distance away.

The marks where paintballs had actually hit and burst were visible, but that was only at the beginning; now, concentrated fire was being directed at Sudou and Satou's position.

"Isn't it because you're here, Sudou-kun?"

"...Nah, it's been like this since before I jumped in. In other words, doesn't that mean Class B knew you were the VIP before we even started fightin'?"

"H-How...? Really?"

"Probably... They're ignoring the guards and are weirdly obsessed with taking you down."

Sudou was confident he could handle it well if the target was aimed at him.

But with a strategy that so blatantly targeted only Satou, that became difficult.

That was because even Sudou couldn't fend them all off if the other side was prepared to sacrifice two or three people.

"Maybe they figured out the VIP's identity somehow... and what's worse, maybe everyone's—"

"Can they do something like that? M-Maybe... it got exposed when Ayanokouji-kun came here!?"

"I guess it's true he might've unconsciously protected the VIP, but where were you then?"

"U-Uhm. I was right inside the tent—-I was scared, so I just stayed hidden..."

Hearing her words, Sudou broke out in a cold sweat as a certain possibility came to his mind.

But right then, whether or not the answer was correct meant nothing.

"I... I don't think I can get away. At least you should run, Sudou-kun and protect the other VIPs—"

"If that's what it takes to win, maybe that's what I should do. But I'm not gonna let 'em take you out this easily... We just gotta fight!"

The accuracy of the incoming shots was by no means high.

Sudou surmised that the skill of the unseen enemy guards wasn't great.

He'd leap out, betting it all and take down all the enemies before Satou was shot.

Having made his decision, Sudou leaped out in front of the enemy.
